1
00:00:03,703 --> 00:00:08,710
Really, all of us, everyone,

2
00:00:09,344 --> 00:00:13,318
has some internal dialogue
with divinity—

3
00:00:14,111 --> 00:00:15,769
the long and short of it.

4
00:00:16,262 --> 00:00:18,430
[Secret Sharer]

5
00:00:19,154 --> 00:00:20,694
Everyone does,

6
00:00:20,694 --> 00:00:24,023
even atheists have 
a dialog with divinity,

7
00:00:24,023 --> 00:00:26,726
but that’s another subject.

8
00:00:27,615 --> 00:00:32,705
So, we have this
internal awareness also.

9
00:00:32,705 --> 00:00:34,969
You know, Paramātmā,
all of that,

10
00:00:34,969 --> 00:00:38,420
this is not just something
you read about it in a book

11
00:00:38,420 --> 00:00:41,680
or see on an interesting poster.

12
00:00:43,070 --> 00:00:46,838
We all have a sense of 
a presence of another

13
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:49,397
who’s observing our life, 
our existence,

14
00:00:49,397 --> 00:00:51,853
what we think, feel,
everything.

15
00:00:51,853 --> 00:00:55,896
Everybody does, it’s just a fact.

16
00:00:56,546 --> 00:00:59,404
I’m not here to argue this point,

17
00:00:59,404 --> 00:01:02,862
just to acknowledge it.

18
00:01:02,862 --> 00:01:06,824
We have some
internal thoughts going on

19
00:01:06,824 --> 00:01:10,096
and the sense of an observer;

20
00:01:10,096 --> 00:01:13,460
upadraṣṭānumantā cha
bhartā bhoktā maheśvaraḥ

21
00:01:13,460 --> 00:01:18,946
paramātmeti chāpy ukto
dehe ’smin puruṣaḥ paraḥ—

22
00:01:19,836 --> 00:01:21,590
Bhagavad–gītā (13.23).

23
00:01:21,590 --> 00:01:25,807
So the dehī, dehinaḥ;
you know, dehinaḥ and dehinī,

24
00:01:25,807 --> 00:01:34,733
those who are embodied,
have this sense of that.

25
00:01:35,951 --> 00:01:39,171
The word ‘companion’ would imply

26
00:01:39,171 --> 00:01:44,049
some sort of affection, almost …

27
00:01:45,144 --> 00:01:48,003
an observer, the overseer. 

28
00:01:48,501 --> 00:01:54,292
Guru Mahārāj, in sort of summarizing that, 
he said,

29
00:01:54,292 --> 00:01:58,671
“Oh, I wasted another day,

30
00:02:00,103 --> 00:02:02,665
so many opportunities were before me

31
00:02:02,665 --> 00:02:05,237
where I could have served.
I wasted my time.

32
00:02:05,237 --> 00:02:09,008
I wasted my time, 
I’m wasting my life.

33
00:02:10,314 --> 00:02:15,123
So, today let me use my life
for something valuable.

34
00:02:22,598 --> 00:02:29,845
That sort of inner dialogue will loop in

35
00:02:29,845 --> 00:02:34,261
the heart and consciousness of 
an aspiring servitor. 

